"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:6.2.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">6.2.1</span> 標題：下襬、衣角（hem, corner of a garment）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： כָּנָף</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kanaf)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:12\">DEU 22:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:1\">DEU 23:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:20\">DEU 27:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:9\">RUT 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:27\">1SA 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:6\">1SA 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:34\">JER 2:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:3\">EZK 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:12\">HAG 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:12\">HAG 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0007_pharisee_hant.png\" alt=\"流蘇和下襬\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">流蘇和下襬 (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>下襬是外衣最下面的褶邊（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">6.2 外衣、外袍、披風、長袍 (outer garment, cloak, mantle, robe)&lt;REALIA:6.2&gt;</a> ）。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>大多數譯本將<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:12\">DEU 22:12</a> 中的希伯來文<em>kanaf</em> 翻譯為「衣角」（“corners”，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a> 將這個詞翻譯為“bottom edge”（「下襬」），也可以作為參考。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a> ：希伯來文<em>kanaf</em> 表示衣服的下襬，有時也用來指整件衣服（比較<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:34\">JER 2:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a> ）。在這些經文中，翻譯者可以選擇一個表示外衣的詞。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a> 的第一個部分可以譯作：「在那些日子，十個來自不同語言的國家的人會抓住一個猶太人的衣服」（“When this happens, ten people from nations with different languages will grab a Jew by his clothes”，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ），或「那時，來自不同國家的十個人會來抓住一個猶太人的外衣」（“At that time, ten men from different countries will come and take hold of a Judean by his coat”，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> ）；另外也可以譯成：「在那些日子裡，十個外國人要來找一個猶太人」（“In those days ten foreigners will come to one Jew”，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ），不過這就喪失了抓住外衣所表達出來的緊迫感。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
